HELP=$"
progress	[spell] [pro]	 	set or display spell version progress"

LONG=$"
Spells can be written to support more than a single version.
The progress command can be used to select version progress for spells.
A spell without an explicit version progress
will use stable version progress.

If a spell should only be updated
when the release fixes security problems
then the secure progress should be selected.

Spells with unstable versions progress
sometimes do not download and often do not compile.
However, the SA is welcome to try them.
Sometimes using unstable versions of xorg drivers will
avoid problems or bugs in the stable releases.

Version progress can be used to indicate
that a spell should never be installed.
A spell with \"exile\" as version progress
will never be installed.

Lastly, a custom version progress can be specified.
A custom version changes only when the SA changes it.

Examples:
# augur progress cherokee custom 1.2.5		set to   custom  version.
# augur progress libgnome unstable		set to unstable progress.
# augur progress xmessage stable		set to   stable progress.
# augur progress named    secure		set to   secure progress.
# augur progress DirectFB exile			prevent     installation.
"

param(){
 if   [[ -n $1 ]]
 then show_installed | grep -i "^$1"
 else show_installed
 fi
}

run(){
 local PL=$PROGRESS_LOGS
 local TO=$PL/$1
 mkdir_p  $PL

 if   [[ -z $1 ]]; then
  grep -r .        $PL |
  sed "s/:/$TAB/;s:$PL/::"

 elif [[ -z $2 ]]; then
  [[ -s            $TO ]] &&
  read <           $TO    &&
  echo "$REPLY"

 elif [[    $2 == stable ]]; then
  rm -f  $TO

 elif [[ -z $3 ]]
 then   echo    "$2" > $TO
 else ( echo -n "$2"; shift 2; printf "\t%s" "$@"; echo; ) > $TO
 fi

 if   [[ -n            $2 ]] &&
      [[ -n            $1 ]] &&
      [[ -f  $GRIMOIRE/$1 ]]
 then
  touch "$GRIMOIRE/$1"
  LC_ALL=C grep -lr "inherit .*$1" $GRIMOIRE |
  LC_ALL=C sed '\,/\.svn/,d' |
  xargs -r --max-lines=256 touch   
 fi
}
